# Continental Idle — Cascade Rules

## Project Info
- Vue 3 + TypeScript + Vite
- Idle/incremental game with 37 themes, prestige system, takeover mechanics
- Engine files in `src/engine/`, components in `src/components/`, data in `src/data/`, types in `src/types/`

## Code Style
- Use BEM naming with hyphens only (e.g. `building-card__name--active`)
- Use single commands, do not chain with &&
- Do not create HTML doctype files
- Read all instruction files before starting work
- Do not repeat yourself

## Architecture Rules
- Engine modules must not import Vue components (one-way dependency: components -> engine)
- All game state mutations go through `gameState.get()` — never cache state references across ticks
- Event bus (`eventBus`) is the only inter-module communication channel
- Save/load logic lives exclusively in `game-state.ts`
- New state fields must be added to `createDefaultState()` and `migrate()` in `game-state.ts`
- Checksum in `computeChecksumFor()` must cover all economically relevant fields

## Audit Discipline
- Always think step-by-step before coding — outline approach first
- Write production-quality code, not tutorial code
- Anticipate edge cases and handle them explicitly
- Prefer explicit over implicit — no magic, no clever one-liners that hurt readability
- Add comments only where the "why" isn't obvious from the code itself
- After writing code, review it yourself and fix any issues you spot
- If you see a better architectural approach than what was asked, mention it briefly
- Do not stop at the first issue — analyze all files, execution paths, async flows, and state transitions

### Pre-Analysis Protocol (3 Passes)
- **Pass 1 — Static Analysis:** Read every file cold. Trace imports, type annotations, function signatures, constants, CSS/HTML issues
- **Pass 2 — Runtime Path Simulation:** Mentally execute the program. Trace async flows, state transitions, external input validation, error boundaries
- **Pass 3 — Adversarial Review:** Assume hostile input (`null`, `""`, `NaN`, `Infinity`, `{}`, `[]`, 10MB strings), wrong async ordering, corrupted/missing localStorage, spam clicks, 24h uptime, tab close mid-save, injection attempts

### Audit Categories (12)
1. **Correctness & Logic:** Edge-case failures, off-by-one, operator precedence, state mutation side effects, unhandled exceptions, `==` vs `===`, missing `break`, shadowed variables
2. **Security:** Injection (XSS, prototype pollution), access control, data leaks, unsafe deserialization (`eval()`, `Function()`, `JSON.parse()` without schema), missing validation
3. **Concurrency & Async:** Race conditions, deadlocks, missing `await`, error-swallowing `.then()`, `Promise.all` vs `allSettled` misuse, stale closures, `setTimeout`/`setInterval` accumulation
4. **Performance:** Memory leaks, blocking I/O, infinite loops, O(N²)+, unnecessary re-renders, polling without cleanup
5. **UI/UX Coverage:** Feature vs Interface checklist table — verify every feature has UI, loading/error/empty states. Flag any engine logic with no user-facing interface
6. **Game Balance & Economy:** Cost growth curves, income scaling, prestige multipliers, NaN/Infinity/negative values, soft/hard caps, exploit vectors (double-purchase, negative-cost), time simulation (1h/10h/100h)
7. **Save/Load & Persistence:** Serialization completeness, deserialization safety, schema versioning/migration, corruption recovery, autosave timing, data loss scenarios, state desync after reload
8. **Accessibility & Responsiveness:** Keyboard navigation, ARIA labels, color contrast (4.5:1 body, 3:1 large), mobile breakpoints (320px/375px/768px), touch targets (44×44px minimum)
9. **Dead Code & Unused Systems:** Uncalled functions, unrendered components, unused CSS classes, orphaned event listeners, unused constants, commented-out code, orphaned type definitions
10. **Type Safety:** `any` usage, unsafe `as` casts, missing return types, runtime shape mismatches, absent optional chaining, enum/union exhaustiveness
11. **Dependency & Supply Chain:** Third-party deps audit — outdated/vulnerable versions, unused imports, replaceable with native APIs, unusual permissions
12. **Architectural Debt:** Over-engineered systems, scalability limits (10× load), single structural refactor recommendation, missing systems (error boundary, input sanitization, retry logic)

### Anti-Hallucination Contract
- Every finding must cite exact file + line range + specific token/pattern that is wrong
- If you cannot cite precisely, classify as "Requires Manual Verification" — never assert as confirmed
- Do not invent line numbers or cite patterns you assume exist without seeing them
- If a category is clean, state explicitly with evidence: *"No issues found in [Category]. Verified by tracing [specific path]."*

### Per-Finding Schema
Every finding must include: Severity (Critical/High/Medium/Low/Info), Location, Confidence (0–100%), Exploitability (Trivial/Moderate/Requires conditions), Blast Radius (Isolated/Feature-level/System-wide/Data loss/Security breach), Description, Root Cause, Proposed Fix (production-ready code), Verification Step

### Completeness Requirement
- NOT done until every category is addressed (findings or explicit clean verdict with evidence)
- Feature vs UI Checklist table populated for every feature
- Architectural Debt section written
- Every finding has Confidence, Exploitability, and Blast Radius

## Audit-Fix Loop
- When asked to audit AND fix, run in a continuous loop: audit (3 passes) → report findings → implement fixes → verify build → re-audit
- After each fix pass, run `npx vue-tsc --noEmit` and `npx vite build` to verify
- If new issues are found in re-audit, fix those too — repeat until no new findings
- Only stop when: (a) no new findings, OR (b) user explicitly says to stop
- Keep a todo_list of all findings and their fix status
- Summarize after each pass: what was found, what was fixed, what remains
- No mercy on severity — do not downgrade a Critical finding to spare feelings

## Testing
- Run `npx vue-tsc --noEmit` to type-check before committing
- Run `npx vite build` to verify production build
- Test edge cases: zero currency, max level, prestige reset, save migration
- Test adversarial inputs: `null`, `""`, `NaN`, `Infinity`, `{}`, `[]`, 10MB strings
- Test async edge cases: wrong order resolution, tab close mid-save, corrupted localStorage
- Test long-running sessions: 24h uptime — check for number overflow or negative values

## Game Balance
- Building cost growth: 1.15 (standard), 1.25 (blackMarket), 1.35 (vault)
- Building income growth: 1.07/level
- Inactive theme income: 50% of active
- Offline cap: 8 hours at 50% rate + skill bonuses
- permanentIncomeBonus capped at 10x
- Debt interest: 1%/min, collection: 5%/10s
